# GitHub Pages: `docs/`

This repo publishes **GitHub Pages from `/docs`**. Tracked content includes `docs/index.html`, the embedded HTML demos (`docs/OBDExplorer*.html`), and static examples under **`docs/plots/`**.

## Agent workflow

When work adds or changes something user-visible on the site (new variant HTML, example PNGs, index links, copy updates), **include the matching files under `docs/` in the same commit or PR as the code** when practical. Do not leave `docs/` updates as an afterthought unless the user opts out.

If generating a new example image for `docs/plots/`, add a link from `docs/index.html` in the **Example Plots** section when it is meant to be showcased.
